**<sub><sub>![P1 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P1-orange?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Validate OAuth state in Google callback**

The Google OAuth flow generates a `state` value on the start endpoint, but the callback handler never reads or verifies `state` before exchanging the authorization code. Without state validation bound to the user session/cookie, a login CSRF/account-confusion flow is possible where a victim browser can be forced to complete an attacker-initiated OAuth response.

